IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: THE ORGANIZATION'S GOAL IS TO PROMOTE THE ADVANCEMENT OF REAL ESTATE IN WISCONSIN AND PROVIDE CUTTING EDGE TOOLS TO HELP REALTORS ENJOY A SUCCESSFUL CAREER AND BE COMPETITIVE IN THEIR MARKET.
IRS990.MissionDescription: TO UNITE LOCAL BOARDS OF REALTORS AND INDIVIDUALS IN THE STATE OF WISCONSIN FOR THE PURPOSE OF SERVING ITS MEMBERS BY FURNISHING PROGRAMS AND SERVICES THAT PROMOTE AN ENVIRONMENT IN WHICH ITS MEMBERS MAY SUCCESSFULLY CONDUCT THEIR INDIVIDUAL BUSINESS WHILE SERVING THEIR CLIENTS AND THE PUBLIC WITH THE HIGHEST DEGREE OF PROFESSIONALISM; AND THROUGH COOPERATIVE ACTION, PRESERVE AND ENHANCE THE RIGHT TO OWN, TRANSFER AND USE REAL PROPERTY.
IRS990.Description: PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT: EXPENSES INCURRED TO PROVIDE INFORMATION, EDUCATION AND TRAINING RELATED TO REAL ESTATE LICENSE LAW, DESIGNATIONS, CONVENTIONS, LEGAL UPDATES, FORMS AND MEMBER SERVICES.

Activity2.Description: LEGAL SERVICES/PUBLIC AFFAIRS: EXPENSES INCURRED TO PROVIDE SERVICES FOR LEGISLATIVE ADVOCACY, HOUSING STATISTICS, REAL ESTATE MARKET RESEARCH, EXTERNAL MEDIA ACTIVITIES, INFORMATION, PRODUCTS AND LOBBYING SERVICES RELATED TO LICENSE LAW, PROFESSIONAL STANDARDS, FAIR HOUSING, AND REAL ESTATE PRACTICE.

Activity3.Description: COMMUNICATIONS: EXPENSES INCURRED TO PROVIDE TECHNICAL AND CREATIVE SUPPORT FOR THE ASSOCIATION'S COMMUNICATION AND PROMOTION OBJECTIVES TO MEMBERS AND NONMEMBERS.

Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.Explanation: The Association's income tax filings are subject to audit by various taxing authorities. Open periods subject to audit for federal and Wisconsin purposes are generally the previous three and four years of tax returns filed, respectively. In evaluating the Association's tax provisions and accruals, future taxable income and the reversal of temporary differences, interpretations and tax planning strategies are considered. The Association believes its estimates are appropriate based on current facts and circumstances. Any interest or penalties assessed to the Association are recorded as operating expenses; however, there were no interest or penalties recorded for the years ended September 30, 2010 and 2009.

THE ASSOCIATION HAS MEMBERS FROM WI WITH THE RIGHT TO PARTICIPATE IN THE ORGANIZATION'S GOVERNANACE. THE MEMBERS OF THE ASSOCIATION CONSIST OF SIX CLASSES: (1) MEMBER BOARDS, (2) BOARD MEMBERS, (3) INDIVIDUAL MEMBERS, (4) INSTITUTE AFFILIATE MEMBERS, (5) AFFILIATE MEMBERS, (6) HONORARY MEMBERS. BOARD MEMBERS AND INDIVIDUAL MEMBERS SHALL BE ACTIVE MEMBERS OF THE ASSOCIATION. ANY MEMBER THAT IS A REALTOR MAY ELECT MEMBERS OF THE GOVERNING BODY.

GeneralExplanation.Explanation: ANNUALLY, ALL THE MEMBERS OF CERTAIN COMMITTEES AND THE BOARD, INCLUDING OFFICERS, ARE GIVEN A FORM TO DISCLOSE ALL CONFLICTS OF INTEREST AND SIGN. THE SIGNED FORMS ARE KEPT AT THE ASSOCIATION'S OFFICE. IN ADDITION, AT THE BEGINNING OF EACH MEETING THE CHAIRMAN ASKS THE MEMBERS IF THEY HAVE ANY CONFLICTS WITH ITEMS ON THE PROPOSED AGENDA. KEY EMPLOYEES ARE NOT REQUIRED TO DISCLOSE THIS INFORMATION.
